#: ../../../reference/generated/numpy.ogrid.rst:4
msgid "numpy.ogrid"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.ogrid:2
msgid "An instance which returns an open multi-dimensional \"meshgrid\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.ogrid:4
msgid ""
"An instance which returns an open (i.e. not fleshed out) mesh-grid when "
"indexed, so that only one dimension of each returned array is greater than "
"1.  The dimension and number of the output arrays are equal to the number of "
"indexing dimensions.  If the step length is not a complex number, then the "
"stop is not inclusive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../docstring of numpy.ogrid:10
msgid ""
"However, if the step length is a **complex number** (e.g. 5j), then the "
"integer part of its magnitude is interpreted as specifying the number of "
"points to create between the start and stop values, where the stop value "
"**is inclusive**."
msgstr ""

